# Conventional Commits

All commits must follow the [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) specification. This project uses semantic-release to automate versioning and changelogs based on commit messages.

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <short summary>

[optional body]

[optional footer]
```

## Types

| Type | When to use |
|------|-------------|
| `feat` | New feature (triggers minor release) |
| `fix` | Bug fix (triggers patch release) |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `refactor` | Code change with no feature/fix |
| `chore` | Tooling, deps, config changes |
| `test` | Adding or updating tests |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `ci` | CI/CD changes |

Breaking changes: add `!` after the type (`feat!:`) or include `BREAKING CHANGE:` in the footer — triggers a major release.

## Examples

```
feat(lists): add Radarr export endpoint
fix(plex): handle missing server gracefully
docs: expand README quick start section
chore: install semantic-release
feat!: require authentication for all list endpoints
```

## Rules

- Summary is lowercase, no period at the end
- Use imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
- Scope is optional but encouraged (e.g. `auth`, `lists`, `plex`, `search`)
- Keep the summary under 72 characters
